# Pillar — Cost Optimization

Module 13 in depth; the checklist in brief:

- **Right-size weekly** — Compute Optimizer + Trusted Advisor + Cost Explorer
- **Commit on the base** — Compute Savings Plans (60–70%) · RIs for stable RDS/cache
- **Spot** for burst — batch, CI, stateless
- **Storage lifecycle** — S3 Intelligent-Tiering, EBS gp3 > gp2, delete unattached
- **Idle elimination** — auto-shutdown dev/test, scheduled off-hours
- **Tag governance** — `cost-center` / `environment` / `owner`; Cost Explorer pivots
- **Anomaly detection day one** — catches the cryptominer before the bill

## Principles

Consumption model · measure efficiency · managed over heavy-lifting · **attribute spend** (tags)

**Insight:** cost is an **operating discipline, not a one-time project** — weekly review beats an annual cleanup.
